‘James’, the man who emailed Mr Jobs, lost his 24-year-old girlfriend in April 2008 to melanoma skin cancer that spread to her liver.

He wanted to thank Mr Jobs for supporting organ donation at Lucile Packard's Children's Hospital in Palo Alto, California.

‘My girlfriend and I are from Cupertino, since childhood, and it's really nice to see the hometown hero take time out to do this,’ he wrote.

The email was revealed by Business Insider and has been revisited by CNN technology writer Mark Milian’s new book on Mr Jobs’s email inbox.

