‘No one wants to die. Even people who want to go to heaven don't want to die to get there. And yet death is the destination we all share.’

Ten years prior to that Mr Jobs told the Computerworld Honors Program he only worried about leaving behind his friends, children and work.

‘We're all going to be dead soon,’ he said. ‘You never know when you're going to go, but you are going to go pretty soon.’

Mr Jobs, who underwent a liver transplant in 2009, died last month aged 56 after a seven-year battle with pancreatic cancer.

